The paper deals with the optimization of multiple-description lattice vector quantizers for packet-lossy channels, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and multimedia (cs.MM) aspects. The paper also discusses the distribution of bits among the descriptions, which falls under the category of statistical learning (cs.LG). The use of lattice vector quantization and optimization techniques suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the areas of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and signal processing (cs.SI).
